RED FLAG 4 — Cell rendering (blank vs NA vs 0 vs value)
═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

Symptom: inconsistent cell rendering across component × solvent matrix.

Fix in build_rs_payload solvent_matrix_tables cell_status assignment:

Four-state rule (universal):
- matched_annexure AND numeric evidence for this solvent → "value"
  Render: computed exposure value with 3-4 decimals
- matched_annexure AND negative_declaration (excluded by process) → 
  "confirmed_zero" → Render: "0" or "0.000"
- matched_annexure AND no evidence for this specific solvent → 
  "not_applicable" → Render: "NA"
- no matched_annexure → "unresolved" → Render: blank + add to 
  manual_review list

Additional q.s. row handling:
- q.s. rows in ALL solvent columns render "NA" (amount cannot be quantified)
- q.s. rows in Quantity/unit column render raw text ("q.s.", "Qs to 1 mL", 
  "Qs to adjust pH")

Rule is universal across all products. Only per-product data varies.

Acceptance for Epinephrine:
- Chlorobutanol × Methanol: annexure doesn't mention Methanol → "NA" ✓
- Chlorobutanol × Acetone: annexure has NMT 5000 ppm → 0.210 mg ✓
- Chlorobutanol × Chloroform: annexure has NMT 60 ppm → 0.003 mg ✓
- Sodium Chloride × Methanol: negative declaration → "0.000" ✓
- Water for Injection q.s. row: "NA" in all solvent cells ✓

