RED FLAG 5 — PDE derivation for non-master solvents
═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

Symptom: Benzene USP <467> Option 2 PDE shows "NA". Approved shows 0.02 
mg/day. Some solvents lack explicit PDE in RSM master.

Root cause: RSM only stores explicit PDE values. Non-USP solvents (CPME, TFA)
and some standard solvents lack explicit PDE mapping.

Fix in RSM.get_pde_mg_day():
If canonical PDE not explicitly defined but concentration_limit_ppm defined:
    calculated_pde_mg_day = concentration_limit_ppm × 10 / 1000
    (assumes USP <467> Option 1 reference of 10 g/day)
Return with source = "option1_derived".

Universal formula. Works for any solvent with a concentration limit.

Acceptance:
- Benzene: 2 ppm × 10 / 1000 = 0.02 mg/day PDE ✓
- CPME: 1500 ppm × 10 / 1000 = 15 mg/day PDE
- TFA: 3400 ppm × 10 / 1000 = 34 mg/day PDE
- All solvents in RSM master keep their explicit PDE values
- Non-master solvents derive from ppm limit

