RED FLAG 7 — Non-USP <467> solvent inclusion
═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

Symptom: solvents with numeric evidence but no canonical match in RSM are 
silently dropped. Trilaciclib loses CPME (1500 ppm) and TFA (3400 ppm). 
Epinephrine loses Chloroform for a while (before recent fix).

Fix in process_rs_annexure:
When solvent has numeric evidence (evidence_type in numerical_limit/nmt/
percentage_limit) but RSM.resolve_solvent() returns None:
- Keep entry in solvents[] with canonical=None, is_non_usp_solvent=True
- Do NOT push to declaration_scopes

Fix in _annexure_solvent_universe:
- Include solvents where canonical=None but converted_ppm is not None
- Use raw solvent_name (title-cased) as display name

Fix in calculate_rs_exposures:
For non-USP solvents:
- Compute exposure = amount × ppm / 1,000,000 (universal formula)
- USP <467> comparison row shows "N/A" for concentration limit
- USP <467> comparison row shows "N/A" for PDE (or user-provided if known)
- cell_status = "value" (not blank)

Rule is universal. Any solvent with numeric evidence gets included.

