RED FLAG 9 — Metadata polish (strength display + overage)
═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

Symptom: Strength shows overage-inclusive value (1.1 mg/mL). Approved shows 
label strength (1 mg/mL).

Fix strength display for overage products:
Display EFFECTIVE (label) strength, not formulation strength.
- Detection: strength value has "*", "**" or note contains "overage"
- Effective strength = api_qty_per_unit / (1 + overage_pct)
- Add footnote: "* API strength inclusive of X% overage"

For non-overage products: display strength as-is.

Universal rule. Overage detection is per-product.

Acceptance for Epinephrine:
- Detected overage: 10% (from "1.10*" footnote)
- Effective strength = 1.1 / 1.10 = 1.00
- Display: "1 mg/mL Epinephrine USP (spec-1)*"
- Footnote: "* API strength inclusive of 10% overage"

